Combining two 'extracted' items usually yields 60, and combining an 'extracted' item with a 'poorly-filtered extract' (made by filtering an extract) can yield 80. Avoid combining more than two items, as this often leads to 'overcomplicated' items and a sharp drop in value.

message: The most consistent way to score 100 points is to first create a magical extract and a mundane extract, then combine them. Use the 'vial' tool on any solid magical ingredient (e.g., dragon scale, unicorn horn) to make a magical extract. Similarly, use the 'vial' on any solid mundane ingredient (e.g., dandelion, amber, frog leg) to make a mundane extract. Combining these two extracts (one magical, one mundane) consistently yielded 100 points. The 'filter' tool was generally less effective for achieving 100, sometimes even decreasing value or introducing negative features like 'botched filtering'.
